# Waste Data Quality System Design

## Current Architecture

The current system processes CSV waste datasets using modular validation logic.

Main components:

- app.py → Streamlit dashboard interface
- validator.py → reusable validation and cleaning logic
- test_validator.py → automated validation tests
- requirements.txt → dependency management
- Dockerfile → deployment portability

## Validation Rules

Current validation includes:

- Removing records with invalid quantity values
- Removing records with missing locations
- Generating quality reports and metrics

## Scalability Direction

The validation logic is intentionally separated from the UI layer to support future scalability.

Possible future extensions:

- REST API integration
- Real-time streaming validation
- Kafka or MQTT event ingestion
- Cloud/Edge deployment using Docker containers
- Distributed validation pipelines

## Reliability Approach

Reliability is improved through:

- Modular validation rules
- Automated testing
- Structured reporting
- Consistent data quality metrics

